    <tags>log-viewer grafana loki victorialogs qt qml logs observability admin</tags>
    <summary>Native desktop log viewer for Grafana with Loki and VictoriaLogs datasources.</summary>
    <description>
LogViewer is a native, high-performance desktop application for browsing and analyzing logs served by Grafana with Loki or VictoriaLogs as the datasource. Built with Qt 6 and C++20, it offers a fast, responsive UI with dark and light themes.

## Features

* Browse, filter, and search logs from any Grafana datasource that speaks Loki/LogsQL.
* Adaptive log table with multi-line message wrapping on narrow windows and inline detail expansion.
* Quick time-range picker with relative presets (last 5 min — last 7 days, Today) and absolute From/To selection.
* Stream/namespace/app discovery with auto-detection of common label keys.
* LogsQL-aware filter syntax with safe escaping for special characters.
* Page-based pagination with First / Newer / Older / Last navigation.
* Available-fields drawer for one-click filter toggling.
* Light and dark themes; choice persists between sessions.

## Source

This is an installer-style Chocolatey package — it downloads the official Windows installer published on the [GitHub Release page](https://github.com/bakhritdinov/log-viewer/releases) and runs it silently. The installer's package source — including the build pipeline that generates this `.nupkg` — lives at https://github.com/bakhritdinov/log-viewer.
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/bakhritdinov/log-viewer/releases/tag/v[[VERSION]]</releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <file src="tools\**" target="tools" />
    <file src="..\..\LICENSE" target="LICENSE" />
  </files>
</package>
